						<summary>

						<p>Uttarāpatīśvara temple, main <hi rend="italic">gōpuram,</hi> left of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman Tribhuvanachakravartti Rājādhirāja (II) •••••</hi></p>						

						<p>This record is fragmentary with the continuations of the available six lines and the portion after the sixth line having been lost. It opens with the king's <hi rend="italic">meykīrtti, Kaḍal-śūḻnda pār-mādarum.</hi> </p>						

						<p>It records some benefaction by Āṭkoṇḍa-nāyakaṉ the <hi rend="italic">araiyaṇ</hi> of Kaḍuvaṉguḍi in [Ti]ruvindaḷūr-nāḍu.</p>						

